Question

A ship sailed 6.9 miles in a direction of 36° North of East. The ship turned and sailed 5.3 miles in a direction 78° North of East.


The ship’s captain suffers a terrible accident. The first officer radios for help and sets anchor, waiting for help while administering first aid.

A helicopter, starting where the ship started, wishes to fly directly to the ship. What direction (\(\theta\) rounded to nearest degree) and distance (\(r\) rounded to nearest tenth of a mile) should the helicopter fly?


  • The direction: \(\theta =\) ##ANSWER1##
  • The distance: \(r =\) ##ANSWER2##

Answerlist

  • 53°

  • 54°

  • 55°

  • 56°

  • 57°

  • 58°

  • 59°

  • 10.8 mi

  • 10.9 mi

  • 11.0 mi

  • 11.1 mi

  • 11.4 mi

  • 11.5 mi

Solution

Start by naming some lengths (the legs of the two small triangles).


Evaluate \(a\), \(b\), \(j\), and \(k\). Remember to set your calculator to DEGREE MODE.

\[a ~=~ 6.9 \cos(36^\circ) ~=~ 5.5822173\] \[b ~=~ 6.9 \sin(36^\circ) ~=~ 4.0557182\] \[j ~=~ 5.3 \cos(78^\circ) ~=~ 1.101932\] \[k ~=~ 5.3 \sin(78^\circ) ~=~ 5.1841823\]

Name the lengths of the large triangle.


Calculate \(x\) and \(y\).

\[x~=~5.5822173+1.101932~=~6.6841492\] \[y~=~4.0557182+5.1841823~=~9.2399005\] Calculate \(\theta\). Remember to set your calculator to DEGREE MODE.

\[\theta ~=~ \arctan\left(\frac{9.2399005}{6.6841492}\right) ~=~ 54.1180017^\circ ~\approx~ 54^\circ\]

Calculate \(r\) by using Pythagorean Theorem.

\[r ~=~ \sqrt{6.6841492^2+9.2399005^2} ~=~ 11.4041051 ~\approx~ 11.4 ~\mathrm{mi}\]

Instead of using Pythagorean Theorem, you could have used trigonometry.

\[r ~=~ \frac{6.6841492}{\cos(54.1180017^\circ)} ~=~ \frac{9.2399005}{\sin(54.1180017^\circ)} ~=~ 11.4041051 ~\approx~ 11.4~\mathrm{mi}\]
